Sentencas: To realize solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) operating in 500-700 degrees C, it is imperative to cultivate innovative cathodes endowed with elevated electrochemical properties.
Titulo: Evaluation of LnCaCoO4+δ as Potential Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Herein, a series of rare-earth oxides LnCaCoO(4+delta) (LnCCO, Ln = Pr, Nd, Sm) are synthesized and assessed as possible SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: Evaluation of LnCaCoO4+δ as Potential Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The crystal structure, oxygen adsorption and desorption behavior, electrochemical activity, and oxygen reduction reaction kinetics of the LnCCO are systematically characterized.
Titulo: Evaluation of LnCaCoO4+δ as Potential Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: LnCCO adopts a tetragonal crystalline structure with an I4/mmm spatial symmetry group.
Titulo: Evaluation of LnCaCoO4+δ as Potential Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The measurement results show that both the cell volume and the conductivity of LnCCO increase gradually with the enlargement of the rare-earth element radius.
Titulo: Evaluation of LnCaCoO4+δ as Potential Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results of XPS and iodometric titration confirm the monotonic increase of interstitial oxygen content and the surface oxygen adsorption ability, when the rare-earth element changes from Sm to Pr in LnCCO.
Titulo: Evaluation of LnCaCoO4+δ as Potential Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical measurement results show that the polarization resistance of PrCaCoO4 is 0.048 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, and the anode-supported cell demonstrates a maximum peak power density of 852 mW cm(2) at 700 degrees C when utilizing dry H-2 as the fuel source.
Titulo: Evaluation of LnCaCoO4+δ as Potential Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The oxygen partial pressure-dependent study proves that the rate-limiting step for ORR on a PrCCO cathode is the adsorption dissociation process of surface oxygen molecules.
Titulo: Evaluation of LnCaCoO4+δ as Potential Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
